summary: An Ordinance amending, Sections 2 and 3 of Ordinance No. 34821, of the City of Seattle approved June 3rd, 1915, and entitled "An Ordinance licensing and regulating the business of peddling and hawking and the conduct of persons engaged therein the City of Seattle, providing penalties for violation thereof" and repealing Sections No's 49, 50, 51, 52, 53, 54 and 55 of Ordinance No. 15855, of the City of Seattle, approved April 25th, 1907.
